20/10/2002
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The Together for Macedonia coalition and the Democratic Union for Integration (DUI) finally have agreed on the composition of the new government. 
DUI will have four ministers and a deputy prime minister. 
Citing party sources, Macedonian Radio reports Abdulhami Kasapi will serve as minister of transportation and communications, Nuhi Dervisi minister of justice, Rexhep Saliku minister of health and Teuta Arifi minister of education. 
The deputy prime minister of the new government would be Musa Xhaferi. 
DUI will also have four deputy seats in the ministries of agriculture, defence, economy and ministry of interior affairs. 
(Trud, AFP - 19/02/02; MIA, Makfax, Reuters - 18/10/02)
